# NCS-Panda

NCS Panda involves designing and developing a web-based E-Portal that allows users to browse menus, place orders, and receive confirmation before reaching the food outlet.

## Setting Up Docker Environments
### Running on Corporate Laptop
1. Press Win + R → type certmgr.msc → Enter
2. Go to Trusted Root Certification Authorities → Certificates.
3. Find the certificate that matches your company/proxy name. e.g. zcaler
4. Right-click it → All Tasks → Export….
5. Wizard:
	No, do not export the private key.
	Base-64 encoded X.509 (.CER).
	Save as zcaler.crt in backend folder
6. docker compose -p ncs-panda -f docker/docker-compose.dev.corp.yml up --build
### Running on Personal Laptop
1. docker compose -p ncs-panda -f docker/docker-compose.dev.yml up --build

## Setting Up Database
1. Run npx prisma migrate dev --name init_database
-  If error perform the below command
```
$env:NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED = "0"
Run npx prisma migrate dev --name init_database
Remove-Item Env:NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED
```
